# ============================================================================
# basal_lock  (Loop next-dev version)
#
# Keeps the temp basal from being throttled below the SCHEDULED basal rate while
# blood glucose is above a configurable threshold (default: off, 250 mg/dL).
#
# NEXT-DEV PORT: DoseMath moved into the standalone LoopAlgorithm package (which
# can't see LoopKit's PreferencesProvider), so the clamp lives in
# LoopDataManager.loop() instead. The Preferences UI is reached from Settings via
# an independent sheet (not the shared `Sheet` enum that the `profiles`
# customization extends), so profiles + basal_lock apply together in either order
# and no combined variant is needed.
#
# Known residual (display only): while locked, the stored dosing decision — and so
# the Nightscout "recommended temp basal" — still shows the algorithm's raw low
# value, not the enforced rate. Nothing enacts from it.
# ============================================================================
